{"id":"5476","name":"Personal 911","tagline":"A shortcut to help you if you might be in trouble at a protest(or anywhere else)","icon":"ios13 c4282601983 g59814","latest":"17570","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>We live in a strange time and people might be finding themselves in situations where they are are worried for their safety. </p>\n<p>Personal 911 is a shortcut you can run to call the people you think might be able to help you if you are in trouble. </p>\n<p>When you activate Personal 911 your phone will progressively call people on you chosen list of emergency contacts so that you can let them know about your situation. If you don’t get through to the person you were calling, hang up and it calls the next person until you reach someone.</p>\n<p>Once you get through, the shortcut creates a text message to that person telling them where you called from (using your Location data).</p>\n<p>If you don’t get through to anyone, there shortcut sends a text to everyone You called letting them know you tried to reach them, couldn’t get through and might be in trouble - it also sends them your location. </p>\n<p>By default the shortcut is set to show you the message before sending it. But it can be set to send the messages automatically by toggling off the show when run action.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>0.1 - June 3, 2020, 6:57 p.m.</strong></p>"}